## Quickstart

```sh
go run . serve                       # start the API {{if .UI}}+ embedded UIs{{end}}
go run . superuser create you@example.com your-password
open http://localhost:8090/_/        # admin dashboard
```

{{if .UI -}}
## Frontend development

```sh
forge dev        # runs the Go API and the SvelteKit dev server together
```

The SvelteKit app lives in `ui/` and proxies `/api` to the Go server.
`make build` bakes the compiled frontend into the single binary.
{{- end}}

## The 30-second tour

- **Collections** (tables) are managed in the admin UI at `/_/` — every
  collection instantly gets a REST API with rule-based permissions.
- **MCP**: create an API key in the admin UI and connect the app to Claude
  or any MCP client — the AI can query data *and* evolve the schema.
- **Modules** are listed in `forge.json`; add more with `forge add`.
- **Settings** (mail provider, OAuth, storage, updates) live in the admin UI.

## Deploying

```sh
make build       # single self-contained binary in dist/
```

Ship the binary (plus nothing else) to a server. Data lives in `./forge_data`.
For fleets of instances, publish releases with `forge release` and let
deployed binaries self-update from the manifest.

## Commands

```
app serve                     start the server
app migrate                   apply migrations and exit
app superuser create E P      manage superusers
app update [--check]          self-update from the release manifest
app backup                    snapshot data + files
```
